work.title: Kantate ved Polyteknisk Læreanstalts 100 Aars Jubilæum
Cantata for the Centenary of the Polytechnic College
Kantate ved Polyteknisk Læreanstalts 100-års jubilæum

history.p: Nielsen mentioned the cantata for the first time in a letter of May 1929. During July he received the text from the poet, and the music was composed in the course of a few weeks at the end of the month. According to Nielsen's diary, the cantata was finished on 5 August. Johannes Andersen undertook the instrumentation of the work and of Fest-Præludium ved Aarhundredskiftet (CNW 84), which was also played at the occasion. The cantata was performed by the Band of the Royal Life Guards.

history.p: This version was used for the first performance at the jubilee celebration in 1929.

incipText.p: En Funke blev tændt i det mægtige Rum
Vort lyse Land, du Drømmenes Syn

expression.title: Version for reciter, male choir, strings and piano

history.p: Already when Carl Nielsen was first approached, there were plans that the new cantata should be performed at the Polytechnic College's future annual celebrations, and he therefore provided a version for choir, reciter, strings and piano. The precise date of the revised version is not known, but it was probably done in autumn 1930.
